The paper presents a new optimization algorithm inspired by the free electron model, which is a common concept in the field of neural networks and machine learning (cs.NE). The algorithm is designed to solve optimization problems, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also involves a theoretical analysis of the algorithm's behavior, which is related to control systems and system dynamics (cs.SY). Finally, the algorithm is tested on benchmark functions, which is a common practice in computational engineering (cs.CE).
